1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,829
This is NANOKAT Forge — a human-gated website planning demo built during OpenAI Build Week.

2
00:00:06,779 --> 00:00:09,714
It is running on Google Cloud Run.

3
00:00:09,714 --> 00:00:17,404
The health check shows Alibaba Model Studio as the provider, and Qwen as the live model — not an offline stub.

4
00:00:17,404 --> 00:00:20,543
I give it a messy small-business brief.

5
00:00:20,543 --> 00:00:22,785
Loose notes are fine.

6
00:00:22,785 --> 00:00:25,271
The system structures them.

7
00:00:25,271 --> 00:00:33,152
Qwen returns a structured plan: business summary, pages, palette, validation steps, and risks.

8
00:00:33,152 --> 00:00:35,597
Nothing is deployed yet.

9
00:00:35,597 --> 00:00:38,641
Consequential work waits for a human.

10
00:00:38,641 --> 00:00:41,942
I approve only when the plan is acceptable.

11
00:00:41,942 --> 00:00:45,910
Without approval, the preview endpoint refuses.

12
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:53,016
After approval, a scoped builder validates constraints and renders an isolated H T M L preview.

13
00:00:53,016 --> 00:00:58,288
No production D N S, no secret access, no site push.

14
00:00:58,288 --> 00:01:02,907
G P T five point six helped with architecture and safety.

15
00:01:02,907 --> 00:01:06,222
Codex implements in-repo when available.

16
00:01:06,222 --> 00:01:09,782
Grok handled host deploy and verification.

17
00:01:09,782 --> 00:01:12,907
Qwen powers the live inference path.

18
00:01:12,907 --> 00:01:21,535
We are not claiming multi-agent Mission Society or cryptographic package signing as shipped today — those are the next vertical slice.

19
00:01:21,535 --> 00:01:27,146
What you see is the working kernel: plan, approve, preview, prove.

20
00:01:27,146 --> 00:01:34,714
NANOKAT Forge: create something useful, know how it was made, and keep a human on the consequential step.

